Script,FinesseSimple
window.currentPBSScenario = 'FinesseSimple';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Finesse_Simple';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for FinesseSimple');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'FinesseSimple',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1[NSH]
*/
# ----- Path 1: South opens 1S (5+ spades, ≤4 hearts), finesse is in hearts -----
p1Shape = spades(south) > 4 and hearts(south) < 5
p1AQH   = hascard(south, AH) and hascard(south, QH) and not hascard(south, KH)
p1N     = spades(north) > 2 and not hascard(north, KH)
path1   = p1Shape and p1AQH and p1N

# ----- Path 2: South opens 1H (5+ hearts, ≤4 spades), finesse is in spades -----
p2Shape = hearts(south) > 4 and spades(south) < 5
p2AQS   = hascard(south, AS) and hascard(south, QS) and not hascard(south, KS)
p2N     = hearts(north) > 2 and not hascard(north, KS)
path2   = p2Shape and p2AQS and p2N

# ----- Common requirements -----
sHcp       = hcp(south) > 13 and hcp(south) < 18
sNoMinor5  = diamonds(south) < 5 and clubs(south) < 5
nHcp       = hcp(north) > 7 and hcp(north) < 12
nNoMinor5  = diamonds(north) < 5 and clubs(north) < 5

# ----- Combine -----
(path1 or path2) and sHcp and sNoMinor5 and nHcp and nNoMinor5

action printoneline,
average "Path 1: 1S, finesse H" 100 * path1,
average "Path 2: 1H, finesse S" 100 * path2,
average "Finesse-K with East  " 100 * ((path1 and hascard(east, KH)) or (path2 and hascard(east, KS))),
average "Finesse-K with West  " 100 * ((path1 and hascard(west, KH)) or (path2 and hascard(west, KS))),
average "South HCP avg        "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP avg        "       hcp(north),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Finesse - Simple,\n\
--- Simple Finesse (3NT，4!H，or 4!S by South)\n\
South opens with a 5+-card major and the partnership reaches a major game\n\
or 3NT. South declares.\n\
\n\
Teaching feature: South holds an AQ in a SIDE suit without the K. The K is in\n\
East or West，roughly half the time each way.\n\
\n\
• When South opens 1!S，the finesse suit is ♥ (AQ-no-K).\n\
• When South opens 1!H，the finesse suit is ♠ (AQ-no-K).\n\
• 5-3-3-2 hands sometimes open 1NT and play 3NT — finesse still applies.\n\
\n\
To take the finesse: lead small from dummy toward South's hand and play the Q\n\
if East follows small. The Q wins about half the time.\n\
\n\
Things to think about:\n\
• Count winners and losers first.\n\
• When in the play should you take the finesse?\n\
• If the finesse loses，where else can you make tricks?\n\
• Did the auction or the opening lead hint where the K sits?\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/finesse.php\n\
%FinesseSimple%
